},
{
“type”: “dialogue”,
“character”: “Maggie”,
“text”: “Finish what I don’t want to say.”
},
{
“type”: “dialogue”,
“character”: “Hetty”,
“text”: “Help her out.”
},
{
“type”: “dialogue”,
“character”: “Harriet”,
“text”: “Oh, yes, introductions will follow the exhibition of my portrait. No doubt I –”
},
{
“type”: “dialogue”,
“character”: “Hetty”,
“text”: “Be patronizing.”
},
{
“type”: “dialogue”,
“character”: “Harriet”,
“text”: “No doubt I shall be able to introduce your husband to his advantage.”
},
{
“type”: “dialogue”,
“character”: “Maggie”,
“text”: “Saved.”
},
{
“type”: “dialogue”,
“character”: “Margaret”,
“text”: “If I find John in a propitious mood I shall take pleasure, for your sake, in telling him about your beauty. Just as you are sitting now would be a lovely pose.”
},
{
“type”: “dialogue”,
“character”: “Maggie”,
“text”: “We can go now.”
},
{
“type”: “dialogue”,
“character”: “Hetty”,
“text”: “Don’t let her think she is doing us a favor.”
},
{
“type”: “dialogue”,
“character”: “Harriet”,
“text”: “It will give me pleasure to add my name to your husband’s list of patronesses.”
},
{
“type”: “dialogue”,
“character”: “Maggie”,
“text”: “Run home and tell John the good news.”
},
{
“type”: “dialogue”,
“character”: “Margaret”,
“text”: “I little guessed when I came for a pleasant chat about old times that it would develop into business arrangements. I had no idea, Harriet, that you had any intention of being painted. By Le Grange, too. Well, I came just in time to rescue you.”
},
{
“type”: “dialogue”,
“character”: “Maggie”,
“text”: “Run home and tell John. Hurry, hurry!”
},
{
“type”: “dialogue”,
“character”: “Hetty”,
